
    Blue Carbon Test Document
    
    This is a test document about blue carbon ecosystems.
    
    Mangroves are important coastal ecosystems that store large amounts of carbon.
    They can sequester up to 10 times more carbon per hectare than terrestrial forests.
    
    Seagrass meadows are another important blue carbon ecosystem.
    They store carbon in both their biomass and in the sediments below.
    
    Salt marshes complete the trio of major blue carbon ecosystems.
    These wetlands are highly productive and store carbon for centuries.
    